### Mini ERP Backend API Requests
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@adminToken =
@userToken =

###
### 1. LOGIN - Get Admin Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loginId": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("adminToken", response.body.token);
%}

###
### 2. LOGIN - Get Sales User Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loginId": "ravi",
  "password": "ravi123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("userToken", response.body.token);
%}

###
### 3. GET CURRENT USER INFO
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 4. GET ALL PRODUCTS
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 5. GET PRODUCT GRAPH (BoM Dependencies)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/graph
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 6. GET SINGLE PRODUCT TREE
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1/graph
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 7. SIMULATE PRODUCT ORDER (What-If Analysis)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1/simulate?qty=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 8. GET SALES ORDERS
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/sales-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 9. CREATE SALES ORDER
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sales-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "customerName": "Rajesh Home Furnishings",
  "lines": [
    {
      "productId": 1,
      "orderedQty": 5
    }
  ]
}

###
### 10. GET PURCHASE ORDERS
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/purchase-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 11. GET MANUFACTURING ORDERS
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/manufacturing-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 12. GET DASHBOARD KPIs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 13. GET AUDIT LOGS
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/audit-logs?page=0&size=20
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 14. GET AUDIT LOG FOR SPECIFIC RECORD
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/audit-logs/record/PRODUCT/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
### 15. H2 Console (Open in browser)
GET {{baseUrl}}/h2-console

###
### Notes:
### - Default H2 Database credentials: sa / (empty password)
### - JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:mem:minierpdb
### - All endpoints require JWT token (except login)
### - Demo data is auto-seeded on first run

